messages.content:
The Eiffel Tower is an iconic iron lattice tower located on the Champ de Mars in Paris, France. Named after the engineer Gustave Eiffel, whose company designed and built the tower, it was constructed as the entrance arch for the 1889 World's Fair (Exposition Universelle), held to celebrate the 100th anniversary of the French Revolution. The Eiffel Tower is one of the most recognizable structures in the world and a global cultural icon of France.

Standing at 324 meters (1,063 feet) tall, it was the tallest man-made structure in the world until the completion of the Chrysler Building in New York City in 1930. The tower has three levels open to the public, with restaurants on the first and second levels and an observation deck on the third level, which offers panoramic views of Paris. The Eiffel Tower is one of the most visited paid monuments in the world, with millions of people ascending it each year.
